All quantum chemical calculations were performed by applying the DFT method with the B3LYP level and 6–31+G (d, p) basis set using Gaussian 09 program package. The structural optimization was determined by minimizing the energy without imposing molecular symmetry constraints. The binding energy of the anion-containing Zn species were defined as the interaction between different molecule fragments, composed of the interaction between Zn2+, TFSI− and Ace. The binding energy E was calculated according to Eq. (1), the expression as follows:1E=Etotal−nE(X)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
